text: "If you can read this in Atlas, heroku is sending the data properly"
"Zorbs are trees with white leaves. Their trunks can be any color and their berries can be any color"
"But I know that can't be quite right"
"Ok, but if I select all the trees with white leaves I should do alright?"
"got it. Is everything with a big fang a moreseth?"
"All the birds (not just Kewps) have head feathers and tail feathers"
"Kewps appear to have purple or orange heads, bodies, head feathers and tail feathers"
"but with a little bit of white"
"so if the bird is all colored, it's not a Kewp"
"for example, if its head and body and wings are purple and its head and tail feathers are orange"
"ok, so it has to have at least one white part?"
"There was one luzack that didn't quite fit the pattern"
"So what I'm about to say isn't entirely correct"
"Neither the petals nor the centers nor the whiskers seem to matter"
"Either in their presence/absence or in their color"
"But we should do ok if we go for spiky stems"
"ok, so the ones with thorny stems are probably luzaks?"
"Ollers are butterflies with white heads and purple legs"
